TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {10252=For QuickIM BlackBerry users: if your BlackBerry is connected to a BES/MDS, you probably don't need to configure GPRS settings. Sometime your administrator needs to open the 2 ports 1863, 1864 on the firewall. If you don't have a BES/MDS connection or you cannot get QuickIM working with it, you can configure your phone's TCP settings (read the forum post here).}
